dcterms:description: This dataset contains extremal graphs that do not have three-cycles or four-cycles, providing foundational results in extremal graph theory.

dcterms:creator: OEIS Foundation Inc.
dcterms:description: This dataset provides the maximal number of edges in n-node graphs that have a girth of at least 5, serving as a reference for extremal graph properties.
dcterms:title: Maximal number of edges in n-node graph of girth at least 5

dcterms:creator: Brendan McKay
dcterms:description: This dataset includes the best-known extremal graphs up to size 64, which are crucial for understanding the bounds in extremal graph theory.
dcterms:title: Best-known graphs up to size 64

dcterms:creator: Brendan McKay
dcterms:description: This dataset consists of graphs that were discovered using incremental tabu search, contributing to the exploration of extremal graph properties.
dcterms:title: Graphs found via incremental tabu search
